Charles Czeisler, a professor of sleep medicine at Harvard Medical School and a specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, designed the course, which he believes is the first of its kind in the United States.
He was inspired to create the course after giving a lecture on the impact sleep deprivation had on learning.
“At the end of the talk, a girl approached me and said, ‘Why are you telling me all this now, in my last year?’
